  "text": "Compared with a small fluorescent organic molecule in solution, the chromophore of FPs is buried within a complex protein environment that influences the photophysical properties of the chromophore through electrostatic interactions. In particular, the internal electric field inside the β-barrel influences the 2P properties of FPs, including the cross section [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Recently, blue-shifted green fluorescent protein homologs have been shown to be 2.5 times brighter than the commonly used enhanced GFP under 2P excitation [CITATION_3] .",
